 <p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:20pt; font-family:ARIAL"><span style="color:#e2231a"><span style="font-weight:bold">Notice of Annual Meeting of Stockholders </span></span></p> <p style="margin-top:16pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">Dear Stockholder: </p> <p style="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">We invite you to attend our 2025 Annual Meeting of Stockholders (&#8220;annual meeting&#8221;) on Thursday, June&#160;12, 2025 at 10:00 a.m., Central Daylight Time (&#8220;CDT&#8221;), at meetnow.global/MGWWKKP, which will be held in virtual-only format. You will not be able to attend the annual meeting in person. At the annual meeting, you will be asked to: </p> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>

<td style="width:2%">&#160;</td>
<td style="width:4%;vertical-align:top;text-align:left"><span style="color:#e2231a"><span style="font-weight:bold">(1)</span></span></td>
<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify"><span style="color:#e2231a"><span style="font-weight:bold"></span></span>Elect five directors, each to serve as a member of the Board of Directors until the next annual meeting of stockholders and until such director&#8217;s successor is elected and qualified; </p></td></tr></table> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>

<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify"><span style="color:#e2231a"><span style="font-weight:bold"></span></span>Transact such other business, if any, as may properly come before the annual meeting and at any postponement or adjournment of the annual meeting. </p></td></tr></table> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">Only stockholders of record and beneficial owners holding our shares as of the close of business on April&#160;21, 2025 (the &#8220;record date&#8221;) are entitled to vote at the annual meeting and any postponement or adjournment thereof. Please see pages 1 &#8211; 5 for additional information regarding attendance at the meeting and how to vote your shares. This Proxy Statement provides information that you should consider when you vote your shares. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">Your vote is important. Even if you plan to attend the annual meeting virtually, we request that you vote your shares as soon as possible by following the voting instructions contained in this Proxy Statement. We have designed the format of the annual meeting to ensure that stockholders are afforded the same rights and opportunities to participate as they would at an <span style="white-space:nowrap">in-person</span> meeting, using online tools to ensure stockholder access and participation. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">By order of the Board of Directors. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">Sincerely, </p> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p> <p style="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-align:justify">

The Notice of Internet Availability instructs you on how to access and review this Proxy Statement and our 2024 Annual Report to Stockholders. The Notice of Internet Availability also instructs you on how you may authorize a proxy to vote your shares over the Internet and provides instructions on how you can request a paper copy of these documents if you desire, and how you can enroll in <span style="white-space:nowrap">e-delivery.</span> If you received your annual meeting materials via email, the email contains voting instructions and links to our annual report and proxy statement on the Internet.</p></td></tr>

<h5 style="font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<div style="text-align:center"><div style="width:8.5in;text-align:left;margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto">

<div style="BORDER-BOTTOM:2.00pt solid #e2231a;BORDER-LEFT:2.00pt solid #e2231a;BORDER-RIGHT:2.00pt solid #e2231a;BORDER-TOP:2.00pt solid #e2231a;MARGIN-LEFT:0px; MARGIN-RIGHT:0px;max-width:100%"><div style="width:97%; margin-top:1.5%; margin-bottom:1.5%; margin-left:1.5%; margin-right:-1.25%">
 <p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold" id="toc894376_1">PROXY STATEMENT SUMMARY </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">To assist you in reviewing the proposals to be considered and voted upon at our 2025 Annual Meeting of the Stockholders (the &#8220;annual meeting&#8221;) we have summarized information contained elsewhere in this Proxy Statement or in our Annual Report on Form <span style="white-space:nowrap">10-K</span> for the fiscal year ended February&#160;1, 2025 (&#8220;Annual Report&#8221;). Please note that our fiscal year is composed of the 52 or 53 weeks ending on the Saturday closest to the last day of January. Fiscal year 2024 consisted of the 52 weeks ended on February&#160;1, 2025 (&#8220;fiscal 2024&#8221;). Fiscal year 2023 consisted of the 53 weeks ended on February&#160;3, 2024 (&#8220;fiscal 2023&#8221;). Fiscal year 2022 consisted of the 52 weeks ended on January&#160;28, 2023 (&#8220;fiscal 2022&#8221;). This summary does not contain all of the information you should consider about the proposals being submitted to stockholders at the annual meeting. We encourage you to read the entire Proxy Statement and Annual Report carefully before voting.&#8195; </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL"><span style="color:#6b6b6b"><span style="font-weight:bold">ANNUAL MEETING OF STOCKHOLDERS </span></span></p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><span style="color:#e2231a"><span style="font-weight:bold"><span style="font-style:italic">Date and Time: </span></span></span></p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">June&#160;12, 2025 </p> <p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">10:00 a.m., Central Daylight Time </p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><span style="color:#e2231a"><span style="font-weight:bold"><span style="font-style:italic">Website: </span></span></span></p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify"><span style="font-style:italic"><span style="font-family:ARIAL;color:#1e3aff"><span style="text-decoration:underline">meetnow.global/MGWWKKP</span></span> </span></p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><span style="color:#e2231a"><span style="font-weight:bold"><span style="font-style:italic">Record Date: </span></span></span></p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">April&#160;21, 2025 </p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><span style="color:#e2231a"><span style="font-weight:bold"><span style="font-style:italic">Anticipated Mailing Date: </span></span></span></p> <p style="margin-top:6pt;  <p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold" id="toc894376_2">INFORMATION ABOUT THE ANNUAL MEETING AND VOTING </p> <p style="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt;width:100%;border-spacing:0;margin:0 auto">

<td style="width:100%"/></tr>


<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt">
<td style="padding-bottom:1pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #e2231a;vertical-align:top"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.58em; text-indent:-1.25em; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold;text-align:justify">1.&#8201;&#8201;What am I Voting on?</p></td></tr>
</table> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The Board of Directors (&#8220;Board&#8221;) of GameStop Corp. (&#8220;GameStop,&#8221; the &#8220;Company,&#8221; &#8220;we,&#8221; &#8220;us,&#8221; or &#8220;our&#8221;) is soliciting your vote for the following: </p> <p style="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;width:100%;border-spacing:0;margin:0 auto">

<td style="vertical-align:top"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL">1. To elect the five nominees identified in this Proxy Statement to serve as directors<br/>&#8195;</p></td>

<td style="vertical-align:bottom">&#160;</td>

<td style="white-space:nowrap;vertical-align:top;text-align:center">FOR ALL<br/> <p style="margin-bottom:1pt; margin-top:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:center">NOMINEES</p></td>
<td style="white-space:nowrap;vertical-align:top"><br/> <p style="margin-bottom:1pt; margin-top:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"></p></td>

</table> <p style="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt;width:100%;border-spacing:0;margin:0 auto">


<tr>

<td style="width:100%"/></tr>


<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt">
<td style="padding-bottom:1pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #e2231a;vertical-align:top"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.58em; text-indent:-1.25em; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold;text-align:justify">2.&#8201;&#8201;Who Is Entitled to Vote?</p></td></tr>
</table> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">Holders of record and beneficial owners of our shares of common stock as of the close of business on April&#160;21, 2025, the record date, are entitled to notice of, and to vote at, the annual meeting. Shares of common stock can be voted only if the stockholder is present or is represented by proxy at the annual meeting. As of the record date, 447,300,514 shares of common stock were issued, outstanding and entitled to vote. </p> <p style="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt;width:100%;border-spacing:0;margin:0 auto">


<tr>

<td style="width:100%"/></tr>


<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt">
<td style="padding-bottom:1pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #e2231a;vertical-align:top"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.58em; text-indent:-1.25em; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold;text-align:justify">3.&#8201;&#8201;How Do I Vote?</p></td></tr>
</table> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify"><span style="font-style:italic">Stockholders of Record</span>. If you are a stockholder of record, there are several ways for you to vote your shares of common stock at the annual meeting: </p> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;border-spacing:0;width:100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid">
<td style="width:4%">&#160;</td>
<td style="width:3%;vertical-align:top;text-align:left"><span style="color:#e2231a">&#8226;</span></td>
<td style="width:1%;vertical-align:top">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify"><span style="font-weight:bold">Voting by Internet. </span>You may vote your shares electronically at the annual meeting by following the instructions on the virtual annual meeting website at<span style="font-weight:bold"> </span>meetnow.global/MGWWKKP. Before the annual meeting you may vote your shares through the Internet by following the directions on the proxy card. Internet voting is available 24 hours a day, and the procedures are designed to authenticate votes cast by using a personal identification number located on the proxy card. The procedures allow you to appoint a proxy to vote your shares and to confirm that your instructions have been properly recorded. </p></td></tr></table> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;border-spacing:0;width:100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid">
<td style="width:4%">&#160;</td>
<td style="width:3%;vertical-align:top;text-align:left"><span style="color:#e2231a">&#8226;</span></td>
<td style="width:1%;vertical-align:top">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify"><span style="font-weight:bold">Voting by Telephone. </span>You may vote your shares by telephone by following the directions on the proxy card. Telephone voting is available 24 hours a day, and the procedures are designed to authenticate votes cast by using a personal identification number located on the proxy card. The procedures allow you to appoint a proxy to vote your shares and to confirm that your instructions have been properly recorded. </p></td></tr></table> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>

<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify"><span style="font-weight:bold">Voting by Mail. </span>If you received a printed copy of your proxy materials, you may vote by mail by completing the enclosed proxy card, dating and signing it, and returning it in the postage-paid envelope provided. If you sign your proxy card and return it without marking any voting instructions, your shares will be voted: (1)&#160;FOR ALL of the director nominees identified in this Proxy Statement; (2)&#160;FOR the approval, on an advisory, <span style="white-space:nowrap">non-binding</span> basis, of the compensation of our Named Executive Officers (&#8220;NEOs&#8221;); and (3)&#160;FOR the ratification of our Audit Committee&#8217;s appointment of KPMG LLP as our independent registered public accounting firm for our fiscal year ending January&#160;31, 2026. </p></td></tr></table> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>

Even if you plan to attend the annual meeting virtually, we recommend that you submit your proxy card by mail or voting instructions via the Internet or by telephone by the applicable deadline so that your vote will be counted if you later decide not to attend the annual meeting. </p></td></tr></table> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify"><span style="font-style:italic">Beneficial Owners</span>. If you are a stockholder whose shares are held in &#8220;street name&#8221; (i.e., in the name of a broker or other custodian) you may vote the shares electronically at the annual meeting only if you obtain a legal proxy from the broker or other custodian </p> <p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">giving you the right to vote the shares. Please see the registration options set forth below under &#8220;Registering in Advance of the </p>

</table> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The annual meeting will be held virtually on Thursday, June&#160;12, 2025 at 10:00 a.m., CDT. Your vote is important, and voting electronically should facilitate the timely receipt of your proxy. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify"><span style="font-style:italic">Stockholders of Record</span>. <div style="text-align:center"><div style="width:8.5in;text-align:left;margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto">

<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;border-spacing:0;width:100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">

<td style="width:4%">&#160;</td>

<td style="width:1%;vertical-align:top">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify"><span style="font-weight:bold">Registering at the Annual Meeting. </span>Visit the virtual annual meeting website at meetnow.global/MGWWKKP for more information on the available options and registration instructions. </p></td></tr></table> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8%; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">We expect that the vast majority of beneficial owners will be able to attend the annual meeting using the control number received with their voting instruction form. Please note, however, that this option is intended to be provided as a convenience to beneficial owners only, and there is no guarantee that this option will be available for every type of beneficial owner voting control number. The inability to provide this option to any or all beneficial owners shall in no way impact the validity of the annual meeting. Beneficial owners may choose the Registering in Advance of the Annual Meeting option above, if they prefer to use this traditional, paper-based option. </p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:8%; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The online meeting will begin promptly at 10:00 a.m., CDT. We encourage you to access the meeting prior to the start time leaving ample time to check in. </p> <p style="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt;width:100%;border-spacing:0;margin:0 auto">


<tr>

<td style="width:100%"/></tr>


<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt">
<td style="padding-bottom:1pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #e2231a;vertical-align:top"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.58em; text-indent:-1.25em; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold;text-align:justify">7.&#8201;&#8201;Do I Need to Register to Attend the Annual Meeting Virtually?</p></td></tr>
</table> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">Registration is only required if you are a beneficial owner, as set forth above. </p> <p style="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt;width:100%;border-spacing:0;margin:0 auto">


<tr>

<td style="width:100%"/></tr>


<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt">
<td style="padding-bottom:1pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #e2231a;vertical-align:top"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.58em; text-indent:-1.25em; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold;text-align:justify">8.&#8201;&#8201;What Constitutes a Quorum?</p></td></tr>
</table> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">A quorum of common stockholders is required to hold a valid annual meeting of stockholders. Unless a quorum is present at the annual meeting, no action may be taken at the annual meeting, except the adjournment thereof to a later time. The holders of a majority of the outstanding shares of our common stock entitled to vote at the meeting must be present or represented by proxy to constitute a quorum. All valid proxies returned will be included in the determination of whether a quorum is present at the annual meeting. The shares of a stockholder whose ballot on any or all proposals is marked as &#8220;abstain&#8221; will be treated as present for quorum purposes. If a broker indicates on the proxy that it does not have discretionary authority as to certain shares to vote on a particular matter, those uninstructed shares, constituting &#8220;broker <span style="white-space:nowrap">non-votes,&#8221;</span> will be considered as present for determining a quorum, but will not be voted with respect to that matter. </p> <p style="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt;width:100%;border-spacing:0;margin:0 auto">


<tr>

<td style="width:100%"/></tr>


<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt">
<td style="padding-bottom:1pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #e2231a;vertical-align:top"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.58em; text-indent:-1.25em; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold;text-align:justify">9.&#8201;&#8201;What Is a Broker <span style="white-space:nowrap">Non-Vote?</span></p></td></tr>
</table> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">A &#8220;broker <span style="white-space:nowrap">non-vote&#8221;</span> occurs when a nominee (such as a custodian or bank) holding shares for a beneficial owner returns a signed proxy but does not vote on a particular proposal because the nominee does not have discretionary voting power with respect to that item and has not received instructions from the beneficial owner. For routine matters, the New York Stock Exchange (the &#8220;NYSE&#8221;) gives brokers the discretion to vote, even if they have not received voting instructions from the beneficial owners. Each broker has its own policies that control whether or not it casts votes for routine matters. In this Proxy Statement, the ratification of our independent registered public accounting firm is expected to be considered routine by the NYSE. </p> <p style="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt;width:100%;border-spacing:0;margin:0 auto">


<tr>

<td style="width:100%"/></tr>


<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt">
<td style="padding-bottom:1pt ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #e2231a;vertical-align:top"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.58em; text-indent:-1.25em; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold;text-align:justify">10.What Vote Is Required to Approve Each Proposal?</p></td></tr>
</table> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify"><span style="font-weight:bold">Voting Rights Generally. </span>Each share of common stock is entitled to one vote on each matter to be voted on at the annual meeting. Stockholders have no cumulative voting rights. Although the advisory vote on Proposal 2 is <span style="white-space:nowrap">non-binding,</span> as provided by law, the Compensation Committee of the Board and the Board will review the results of the vote and, consistent with our record of stockholder engagement, will consider the results of the vote when making future compensation decisions. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify"><span style="font-weight:bold">Election of Directors. </span>Our Bylaws provide that, in an uncontested election, a nominee for director is elected only if such nominee receives the affirmative vote of a majority of the total votes cast for such nominee. The majority voting standard does not apply in contested elections, and directors are elected by a plurality of the votes cast in a contested election. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The majority voting standard will apply to the election of directors at the annual meeting. Accordingly, a nominee for election to the Board will be elected if the number of votes cast &#8220;for&#8221; such nominee exceeds the number of votes cast &#8220;against&#8221; that nominee. Abstentions and broker <span style="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</span> will not be treated as votes cast in the election of a director and will therefore have no effect on the result of such vote. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify"><span style="font-weight:bold">Advisory Vote on Executive Compensation. </span>Approval on an advisory, <span style="white-space:nowrap">non-binding</span> basis of the compensation of our NEOs requires the affirmative vote of a majority of the shares present or represented by proxy and entitled to vote at the annual meeting on this proposal. Abstentions (if any) will have the same effect as a vote &#8220;against&#8221; this proposal. Broker <span style="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</span> (if any) will have no effect on this proposal because they are not entitled to vote on this proposal. As an advisory vote, the proposal to approve the </p>
 <p style="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&#160;</p>

<div style="text-align:center"><div style="width:8.5in;text-align:left;margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto">
 <p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">
compensation of our NEOs is not binding upon us. However, our Compensation Committee, which is responsible for designing and administering our executive compensation programs, and the Board value the opinions expressed by our stockholders and will consider the results of the vote when making future compensation decisions. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify"><span style="font-weight:bold">Ratification of Appointment of Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm. </span>Ratification of our Audit Committee&#8217;s appointment of KPMG LLP (&#8220;KPMG&#8221;) as our independent registered public accounting firm for our fiscal year ending January&#160;31, 2026 requires the affirmative vote of a majority of the shares present or represented by proxy and entitled to vote at the annual meeting on this proposal. Abstentions (if any) will have the same effect as a vote &#8220;against&#8221; this proposal. The approval of this proposal is a routine matter on which a broker or other nominee is generally empowered to vote in the absence of voting instructions from the beneficial owner, so broker <span style="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</span> are unlikely to result from this proposal. Broker <span style="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</span> (if any) will have no effect on the outcome of this proposal because they are not entitled to vote on this proposal. If the stockholders should not ratify the appointment of KPMG, the Audit Committee will reconsider the appointment. </p> <p style="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>

</table> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">We have engaged Computershare, our transfer agent, to act as our independent tabulator to receive and tabulate votes and to act as our inspector of election. See &#8220;Other Matters&#8212;Other Proposals and Nominees&#8221; later in this Proxy Statement. Proposals should be sent via registered, certified, or express mail to: Secretary, GameStop Corp., 625 Westport Parkway, Grapevine, Texas 76051. </p> <p style="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>

</table> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">Yes. Beginning at least 30 minutes prior to, and during the annual meeting, you will be able to access the Rules of Conduct applicable to the annual meeting. We will hold a Q&amp;A session during the annual meeting, during which we intend to answer questions that are pertinent to the items being brought before the stockholder vote at the annual meeting, as time permits and in accordance with our Rules of Conduct for the annual meeting. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify"><span style="font-style:italic">Stockholders of Record</span>. If you are a stockholder of record, you may submit questions by accessing the meeting site at meetnow.global/MGWWKKP and following the directions. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify"><span style="font-style:italic">Beneficial Owners</span>. If you are a beneficial owner, please see the registration options set forth above under &#8220;6. How Can I Attend the Annual Meeting?&#8221; to submit questions. </p> <p style="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt;width:100%;border-spacing:0;margin:0 auto">


<tr>

<td style="width:100%"/></tr>


<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt">

</table> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">We encourage you to access the meeting site in advance of the annual meeting start time. If you encounter any difficulties accessing the virtual meeting during the <span style="white-space:nowrap">check-in</span> or meeting time, please call the technical support line number that will be posted on the virtual meeting site. </p>

<h5 style="font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<div style="text-align:center"><div style="width:8.5in;text-align:left;margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto">
 <p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold" id="toc894376_3">PROPOSAL 1: <span style="font-family:ARIAL;color:#e2231a">ELECTION OF DIRECTORS</span> </p> <p style="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold" id="toc894376_4">Director Nomination Process </p> <p style="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p><div style="line-height:1.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #e2231a">&#160;</div> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The Board has nominated each of the five individuals identified below under &#8220;The Director Nominees&#8221; to stand for election at the annual meeting. Each of the nominees is currently a director of the Company. The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee of the Board determined to not nominate Ms.&#160;Yang Xu for <span style="white-space:nowrap">re-election</span> in order to permit Ms.&#160;Xu to focus on her other business ventures. Such determination was not a result of any disagreement with the Company on any matter relating to the Company&#8217;s operations, policies or practices. The Company thanks Ms.&#160;Xu for her dedicated service on the Board since 2021. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">Each director elected at the annual meeting will hold office for a term expiring at the 2026 annual meeting of stockholders and until his or her successor has been elected and qualified, or until his or her earlier death, resignation or removal. Each of the nominees identified in this Proxy Statement has consented to being named as a nominee in our proxy materials and has accepted the nomination and agreed to serve as a director if elected by the stockholders. We have no reason to believe that any of the nominees will be unable to serve as a director. However, should any nominee be unable to serve if elected, the Board may reduce the number of directors or recommend a substitute nominee. The shares represented by all valid proxies may be voted for the election of a substitute if one is nominated by the Board. </p> <p style="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold" id="toc894376_5">The Director Nominees </p> <p style="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p><div style="line-height:1.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #e2231a">&#160;</div> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The following table sets forth the names and ages of the individuals nominated by the Board for election at the annual meeting, the years they first became a director, the positions, if any, they hold with the Company, and the standing committees of the Board, if any, on which they serve as of April&#160;21, 2025: </p> <p style="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>

<div style="text-align:center"><div style="width:8.5in;text-align:left;margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto">
 <p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold" id="toc894376_7">Biographies of Director Nominees </p> <p style="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p><div style="line-height:1.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #e2231a">&#160;</div> <p style="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The biographies describe each director nominee&#8217;s qualifications and relevant experience. The biographies include key qualifications, skills and attributes most relevant to the decision to nominate candidates to serve on the Board. </p> <p style="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;width:100%;border-spacing:0;margin:0 auto">


<tr>

<td style="width:34%"/>

<td style="vertical-align:bottom;width:1%"/>
<td style="width:65%"/></tr>


<tr style="font-size:1pt;background-color:#e2231a">
<td style="height:3.75pt" colspan="3"/></tr>
<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt;background-color:#e2231a">
<td colspan="3" style="padding-bottom:4pt ;vertical-align:bottom"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:0.64em; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><span style="color:#ffffff"><span style="font-weight:bold">RYAN COHEN - </span><span style="color:#ffffff"><span style="font-style:italic">President, Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of the Board </span></span><span style="color:#ffffff"><span style="font-weight:bold"></span></span></span></p></td></tr>
<tr style="font-size:1pt">
<td style="height:3.75pt"/>
<td style="height:3.75pt" colspan="2"/></tr>
<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<td style="vertical-align:bottom"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.78em; line-height:15.0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><span style="color:#666666"><span style="font-weight:bold">Director Since: <span style="color:#e2231a">2021</span></span></span></p></td>
<td style="vertical-align:bottom">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:bottom"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; line-height:15.0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><span style="color:#666666"><span style="font-weight:bold">Age: <span style="color:#e2231a">39</span></span></span></p></td></tr>
<tr style="font-size:1pt">
<td style="height:6pt"/>
<td style="height:6pt" colspan="2"/></tr>
<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<td style="vertical-align:bottom"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.78em; line-height:20.0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><span style="color:#666666"><span style="font-weight:bold">Other&#160;Public&#160;Company&#160;Directorships:&#8195;&#8195;</span></span></p></td>
<td style="vertical-align:bottom">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:bottom"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; line-height:20.0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><span style="color:#666666">&#8226; None</span></p></td></tr>
<tr style="font-size:1pt">
<td style="height:6pt"/>
<td style="height:6pt" colspan="2"/></tr>
<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<td style="vertical-align:bottom"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.78em; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL"><span style="color:#666666"><span style="font-weight:bold">GameStop Committees:</span></span></p></td>
<td style="vertical-align:bottom">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:bottom"><span style="color:#666666">&#8226; None</span></td></tr>
</table> <p style="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">Ryan Cohen has been a member of the Board since January 2021. He was elected Chairman of the Board in June 2021 and appointed Chief Executive Officer in September 2023. Mr.&#160;Cohen is also a sizable stockholder of the Company. Mr.&#160;Cohen previously founded and served as the Chief Executive Officer of Chewy, Inc. (NYSE: CHWY), where he oversaw the company&#8217;s growth and ascension to market leadership in the pet industry. Mr.&#160;Cohen led Chewy through its successful sale to PetSmart Inc. prior to stepping down in 2018. </p> <p style="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify"><span style="font-style:italic">Director Qualifications</span>: In addition to his ownership perspective, Mr.&#160;Cohen brings to the Board his demonstrated leadership experience as a successful entrepreneur and investor and his extensive experience in retail, technology and consumer marketing verticals, having overseen merchandising, marketing, supply chain, ecommerce and business development. </p> <p style="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>

In his chief financial officer and audit committee chair roles, Mr.&#160;Grube has overseen company cybersecurity readiness assessments, risk reviews, and control effectiveness. </p> <p style="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify"><span style="font-style:italic">Director Qualifications</span>: Mr.&#160;Grube brings to the Board more than two decades of corporate experience, having served in senior management positions overseeing finance, accounting, treasury, tax, and procurement. </p> <p style="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>

</table> <p style="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">Nathaniel Turner is a seasoned entrepreneur and business leader. Mr.&#160;Turner is currently the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Collectors Holdings, Inc., a holding company focused on the collectibles industry. Prior to joining Collectors Holdings, Inc., Mr.&#160;Turner <span style="white-space:nowrap">co-founded,</span> and was the Chief Executive Officer of, Flatiron Health, Inc., a technology company focused on the oncology industry. He also cofounded and led Invite Media, an advertising technology company. Mr.&#160;Turner is an active angel investor and has invested in many startups both personally and through Operator Partners LLC, a venture capital investment firm that invests in early-stage technology companies and founders. Mr.&#160;Turner earned a Bachelor of Science degree in economics from the Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania. </p> <p style="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify"><span style="font-style:italic">Director Qualifications:</span> Mr.&#160;Turner&#8217;s brings to the Board extensive leadership and entrepreneurial experience, having founded several companies, and significant experience in retail, internet services and ecommerce. </p> <p style="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold">THE BOARD UNANIMOUSLY RECOMMENDS THAT STOCKHOLDERS VOTE <span style="text-decoration:underline">FOR ALL</span> OF THE BOARD&#8217;S FIVE NOMINEES. PROXIES SOLICITED BY THIS PROXY STATEMENT WILL BE VOTED <span style="text-decoration:underline">FOR ALL</span> FIVE NOMINEES UNLESS A VOTE AGAINST A NOMINEE OR ABSTENTION IS SPECIFICALLY INDICATED. </p> <p style="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold" id="toc894376_8">The Board of Directors </p> <p style="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p><div style="line-height:1.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #e2231a">&#160;</div> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><span style="color:#e2231a"><span style="font-weight:bold">Board Oversight of Strategy </span></span></p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The Board is deeply engaged and involved in overseeing our long-range strategy, including evaluating key market opportunities, consumer trends and competitive developments as well as capital allocation and deployment strategies. The Board&#8217;s oversight of risk is another integral component of the Board&#8217;s oversight and engagement on strategic matters. Strategy-related matters are regularly discussed at Board meetings and, as relevant, at Board committee meetings. Matters of strategy also inform committee-level discussions of many issues, including business risk and investment decisions. Engagement of the Board on these issues and other matters of strategic importance continues in between Board meetings, including through updates to the Board on significant items. Each director is expected to and does bring to bear his or her own talents, insights and experiences on these strategy discussions. </p>
 <p style="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&#160;</p>

<tr>

<td/>

<h5 style="font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<div style="text-align:center"><div style="width:8.5in;text-align:left;margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto">
 <p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><span style="color:#e2231a"><span style="font-weight:bold">Meetings and Committees of the Board </span></span></p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The Board met five times during fiscal 2024. Each incumbent director who served on the Board at any time during fiscal 2024 attended 75% or more of the aggregate of the total number of meetings of the Board and the total number of meetings of all committees thereof on which they served (held during the period in fiscal 2024 that he or she served). </p> <p style="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The Board has three standing committees: an Audit Committee, a Compensation Committee, and a Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee.&#8195;The Board also has formed an Investment Committee consisting of the Company&#8217;s Chairman of the Board and Chief Executive Officer, Ryan Cohen, and two other members of the Board, to manage the Company&#8217;s portfolio of securities and investments. More information regarding the Investment Committee and our investment policy is included in our 2024 Annual Report on Form <span style="white-space:nowrap">10-K</span> . </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold">Audit Committee </p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The Audit Committee assists the Board in fulfilling its oversight responsibility and reviews: </p> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;border-spacing:0;width:100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">

<td style="width:3%;vertical-align:top;text-align:left"><span style="color:#e2231a">&#8226;</span></td>
<td style="width:1%;vertical-align:top">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify">The adequacy and integrity of our financial statements, financial reporting process and disclosure controls and procedures and internal controls over financial reporting; </p></td></tr></table> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;border-spacing:0;width:100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">

<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify">The scope of the audit performed by the independent registered public accounting firm of our books and records; </p></td></tr></table> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>

<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify">With management and the independent auditor, any related party transactions and approves such transactions, if any. </p></td></tr></table> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">In addition, the Audit Committee has established procedures for the receipt, retention and treatment of confidential and anonymous complaints regarding our accounting, internal accounting controls and auditing matters. The Board has adopted a written charter setting out the functions of the Audit Committee (the &#8220;Audit Committee Charter&#8221;), a copy of which is available on our website at <span style="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;color:#1e3aff"><span style="text-decoration:underline"><span style="font-style:italic">http://investor.gamestop.com/corporate-governance</span></span></span><span style="font-family:ARIAL"> and is available in print to any stockholder who requests it in writing to our Secretary, GameStop Corp., 625 Westport Parkway, Grapevine, Texas 76051. As required by the Audit Committee Charter, the Audit Committee will continue to review and reassess the adequacy of the Audit Committee Charter annually and recommend any changes to the Board for approval. </span></p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The current members of the Audit Committee are Jim Grube (Chair), Alan Attal and Yang Xu, each of whom is an &#8220;independent&#8221; director under the listing standards of the NYSE. The Board has determined that Mr.&#160;Grube has the requisite attributes of an &#8220;audit committee financial expert&#8221; as defined by regulations promulgated by the SEC and that such attributes were acquired through relevant education and/or experience. In addition to meeting the independence standards of the NYSE, each member of the Audit Committee is financially literate and meets the independence standards established by the SEC. The Audit Committee met four times during fiscal 2024. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold">Compensation Committee </p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The Compensation Committee is primarily responsible for: </p> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>

<div style="text-align:center"><div style="width:8.5in;text-align:left;margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto">
 <p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The current members of the Compensation Committee are Alan Attal (Chair), Larry Cheng and Jim Grube, each of whom meets the independence standards of the NYSE and the SEC. The Board has adopted a written charter setting out the functions of the Compensation Committee, a copy of which is available on our website at <span style="font-style:italic"><span style="text-decoration:underline"><span style="font-family:ARIAL;color:#1e3aff">http://investor.gamestop.com/corporate-governance</span></span></span><span style="font-style:italic"> </span>and is available in print to any stockholder who requests it in writing to our Secretary, GameStop Corp., 625 Westport Parkway, Grapevine, Texas 76051. The Compensation Committee met four times during fiscal 2024. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold">Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee </p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee is primarily responsible for: </p> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;border-spacing:0;width:100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid">
<td style="width:4%">&#160;</td>
<td style="width:3%;vertical-align:top;text-align:left"><span style="color:#e2231a">&#8226;</span></td>
<td style="width:1%;vertical-align:top">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify">Reviewing and recommending to the Board candidates for service on the Board and its committees, including the nomination of existing directors; </p></td></tr></table> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;border-spacing:0;width:100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid">
<td style="width:4%">&#160;</td>
<td style="width:3%;vertical-align:top;text-align:left"><span style="color:#e2231a">&#8226;</span></td>
<td style="width:1%;vertical-align:top">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify">Establishing, maintaining and periodically assessing a process for the receipt and consideration of written recommendations for Board candidates in accordance with applicable rules of the NYSE and any other applicable laws, rules and regulations; </p></td></tr></table> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;border-spacing:0;width:100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid">
<td style="width:4%">&#160;</td>
<td style="width:3%;vertical-align:top;text-align:left"><span style="color:#e2231a">&#8226;</span></td>
<td style="width:1%;vertical-align:top">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify">Periodically reviewing and making recommendations to the Board regarding the size and composition of the Board and its committees; </p></td></tr></table> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;border-spacing:0;width:100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid">
<td style="width:4%">&#160;</td>
<td style="width:3%;vertical-align:top;text-align:left"><span style="color:#e2231a">&#8226;</span></td>
<td style="width:1%;vertical-align:top">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify">Annually reviewing the independence of the directors; </p></td></tr></table> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;border-spacing:0;width:100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid">
<td style="width:4%">&#160;</td>
<td style="width:3%;vertical-align:top;text-align:left"><span style="color:#e2231a">&#8226;</span></td>
<td style="width:1%;vertical-align:top">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify">Overseeing our orientation process for newly elected directors and regularly assessing the adequacy of, and need for, additional director continuing education programs; </p></td></tr></table> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;border-spacing:0;width:100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid">
<td style="width:4%">&#160;</td>
<td style="width:3%;vertical-align:top;text-align:left"><span style="color:#e2231a">&#8226;</span></td>
<td style="width:1%;vertical-align:top">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify">Overseeing the annual performance evaluation of the Board and its committees and management; and </p></td></tr></table> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;border-spacing:0;width:100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid">
<td style="width:4%">&#160;</td>
<td style="width:3%;vertical-align:top;text-align:left"><span style="color:#e2231a">&#8226;</span></td>
<td style="width:1%;vertical-align:top">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify">Periodically reviewing and recommending changes to our Corporate Governance Guidelines. </p></td></tr></table> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The current members of the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee are Alan Attal (Chair), Larry Cheng and Yang Xu, each of whom meets the independence standards of the NYSE. The Board has adopted a written charter setting out the functions of the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee, a copy of which can be found on our website at <span style="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;color:#1e3aff"><span style="font-style:italic"><span style="text-decoration:underline">http://investor.gamestop.com/corporate-governance</span></span></span><span style="font-family:ARIAL"><span style="font-style:italic"> </span>and is available in print to any stockholder who requests it in writing to our Secretary, GameStop Corp., 625 Westport Parkway, Grapevine, Texas 76051. The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee met three times during fiscal 2024. </span></p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold">Minimum Qualifications </p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee ensures that the Board possesses the right mix of skills and experiences to provide effective guidance and oversight to management as it executes our short- and long-term strategy. The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee does not set specific minimum qualifications for directors, except to the extent required to meet applicable legal, regulatory and stock exchange requirements, including, but not limited to, the independence requirements of the NYSE and the SEC, as applicable. Instead, we seek nominees for director who possess business acumen, high integrity, an ownership mentality, and a deep, genuine interest in GameStop. The Board also believes that each director should have a basic understanding of (i)&#160;the principal operational and financial objectives and plans and strategies of the Company, (ii)&#160;the results of operations and financial condition of the Company and of any significant subsidiaries or business segments, and (iii)&#160;the relative standing of the Company and its business segments in relation to its competitors. We do not believe diversity, whether of gender, race/ethnicity or any other criteria, is a meaningful basis by which to identify and assess the qualifications of director nominees nor do we seek director nominees purely for the sake of diversity. The Board has established a director retirement age of 75, unless the Chair of the Board grants a waiver as permitted under the retirement policy. Currently, none of our directors is of retirement age. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold">Nominating Process </p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee will consider recommendations for director candidates from a variety of sources (including incumbent directors, stockholders (in accordance with the procedures described below), our management and third-party search firms). When nominating an incumbent director for <span style="white-space:nowrap">re-election</span> at an annual meeting, the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee considers the director&#8217;s performance on the Board and its committees and the director&#8217;s qualifications in light of the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee&#8217;s assessment of the Board&#8217;s needs. The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee has not adopted any criteria for evaluating a candidate for nomination to the Board that differ depending on whether the candidate is nominated by a stockholder, an incumbent director, our management, third-party search firm or other source. </p>
 <p style="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&#160;</p>

<td/>

<td style="vertical-align:bottom;width:1%"/>
<td style="width:98%"/></tr>
<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<td style="vertical-align:bottom;white-space:nowrap"> <p style="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:1pt">


<img src="g894376g85t00.jpg" alt="LOGO" style="width:0.740425in;height:0.149171in"/>
</p></td>
<td style="vertical-align:bottom">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:bottom;white-space:nowrap;text-align:right"> <p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold;text-align:right">2025&#160;Proxy&#160;Statement&#8201;|&#8201;<span style="color:#e2231a">11</span></p></td></tr></table>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always"> </p>
<hr style="color:#999999;height:3px;width:100%;clear:both"/>
<h5 style="font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<div style="text-align:center"><div style="width:8.5in;text-align:left;margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto">
 <p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold">Consideration of Stockholder-Nominated Directors </p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">In addition to proposing a candidate for possible nomination by the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee, any stockholder is entitled to directly nominate one or more candidates for election to the Board in accordance with our Bylaws. See &#8220;Other Matters&#8212;Other Proposals and Nominees&#8221; later in this Proxy Statement. Also, our Bylaws include a proxy access provision, which allows a stockholder, or a group of up to 25 stockholders, owning 3% or more of our outstanding common stock continuously for at least three years, to nominate and include in our proxy materials director nominees constituting up to two individuals or 25% of the Board (whichever is greater), provided that the stockholder(s) and the nominee(s) satisfy the requirements specified in Article III of the Bylaws. The complete text of our Bylaws, as amended, is available on our website at <span style="font-style:italic"><span style="font-family:ARIAL;color:#1e3aff"><span style="text-decoration:underline">http://investor.gamestop.com/corporate-governance</span></span></span> and is available in print to any stockholder who requests it in writing to our Secretary, GameStop Corp., 625 Westport Parkway, Grapevine, Texas 76051. See &#8220;Other Matters&#8212;Proxy Access Director Nominees&#8221; elsewhere in this Proxy Statement. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold">Annual Board Evaluation Process </p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The Board recognizes that a constructive evaluation process is an essential part of good corporate governance and board effectiveness. The evaluation processes utilized by the Board are designed and implemented under the direction of the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee and aim to assess Board and committee effectiveness as well as individual Director performance and contribution levels. The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee and full Board consider the results of these evaluations in connection with their review of director nominees to ensure the Board continues to operate effectively. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">Our directors regularly complete governance questionnaires and self-assessments. These questionnaires and assessments, and feedback from discussions between members of the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee and individual directors, facilitate a candid assessment of: (i)&#160;the Board&#8217;s performance in areas such as business strategy, risk oversight, talent development and succession planning and corporate governance; (ii)&#160;the Board&#8217;s structure, composition and culture; and (iii)&#160;the mix of skills, qualifications and experiences of our directors. </p> <p style="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL;font-weight:bold" id="toc894376_9">Corporate Governance </p> <p style="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p><div style="line-height:1.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #e2231a">&#160;</div> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><span style="color:#e2231a"><span style="font-weight:bold">Director Independence; Independence Determination </span></span></p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The Board has adopted the definition of independence in the listing standards of the NYSE. In its assessment of director independence, the Board considers all commercial, charitable and other relationships and transactions that any director or member of his or her immediate family may have with us, with any of our affiliates or with any of our consultants or advisers. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The Board has affirmatively determined that, during fiscal 2024, each of Alan Attal, Larry Cheng, Jim Grube, and Yang Xu and the Audit Committee, the Compensation Committee and the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee were independent under the NYSE standards as well as under standards set forth in SEC regulations. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The Board has also affirmatively determined that, except for Ryan Cohen and Nat Turner, each of the director nominees is independent under the NYSE standards as well as under standards set forth in SEC regulations, and that the Audit Committee, the Compensation Committee and the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee are composed exclusively of independent directors under the foregoing standards. The Board determined that Mr.&#160;Cohen is not independent because of his current executive position. In November 2024, the Company entered into a collaboration with Collectors Holdings, Inc. (&#8220;Collectors&#8221;), through its Profession Sports Authenticator division (&#8220;PSA&#8221;). The Board determined that Mr.&#160;Turner is not independent due to his role as Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of Collectors. For a description of the collaboration, see &#8220;Certain Relationships and Related Transactions&#8221; below. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">Our independent and <span style="white-space:nowrap">non-management</span> directors hold regularly scheduled executive sessions without management present. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><span style="color:#e2231a"><span style="font-weight:bold">Board Leadership Structure </span></span></p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">In June 2023, the Board appointed Ryan Cohen as Executive Chairman of the Board and Alan Attal as Lead Independent Director. Subsequently, in September 2023, the Board appointed Mr.&#160;Cohen as the Company&#8217;s President, Chief Executive Officer and Chairman. Therefore, the Board&#8217;s leadership structure is currently composed of a combined President, Chief Executive Officer and Chair of the Board and a Lead Independent Director. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">The Board believes that having a combined President, Chief Executive Officer and Chair of the Board enhances the Board&#8217;s oversight of our <span style="white-space:nowrap"><span style="white-space:nowrap">day-to-day</span></span> operations and provides additional management expertise with respect to the complexities of our business units. The establishment and maintenance of the Lead Independent Director role is intended to provide an element of </p>
 <p style="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&#160;</p>
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:12pt;width:100%;border-spacing:0;margin:0 auto">

<td style="vertical-align:bottom;width:1%"/>

<div style="text-align:center"><div style="width:8.5in;text-align:left;margin-left: auto;margin-right: auto">
 <p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">
Board leadership that is separate and distinct from executive management, thereby facilitating robust, independent and objective contributions from the independent directors. The Lead Director&#8217;s principal responsibilities and duties include: </p> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;border-spacing:0;width:100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">

<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify">collaborating with the President, Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of the Board; </p></td></tr></table> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>

<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify">evaluating the performance of the President, Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of the Board in consultation with the committees of the Board, as necessary; </p></td></tr></table> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;border-spacing:0;width:100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid">
<td style="width:4%">&#160;</td>
<td style="width:3%;vertical-align:top;text-align:left"><span style="color:#e2231a">&#8226;</span></td>
<td style="width:1%;vertical-align:top">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify">coordinating the selection and retention of independent consultants and advisors to the Board, as necessary and appropriate; </p></td></tr></table> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;border-spacing:0;width:100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid">
<td style="width:4%">&#160;</td>
<td style="width:3%;vertical-align:top;text-align:left"><span style="color:#e2231a">&#8226;</span></td>
<td style="width:1%;vertical-align:top">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify">discussing Board governance matters with major stockholders and other stakeholders, if requested; and </p></td></tr></table> <p style="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&#160;</p>
<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;border-spacing:0;width:100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
<tr style="page-break-inside:avoid">
<td style="width:4%">&#160;</td>
<td style="width:3%;vertical-align:top;text-align:left"><span style="color:#e2231a">&#8226;</span></td>
<td style="width:1%;vertical-align:top">&#160;</td>
<td style="vertical-align:top;text-align:left"> <p style=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt;text-align:justify">performing such other functions as our Bylaws of the Company provide or as the Board may specify from time to time. </p></td></tr></table> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">In addition, all directors play an active role in overseeing our business both at the Board and committee level. This structure, together with our other corporate governance practices, provides independent oversight of management while ensuring clear strategic direction for us. The Board believes that at this time our stockholders are best served by this structure. </p> <p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><span style="color:#e2231a"><span style="font-weight:bold">Majority Voting in the Election of Directors </span></span></p> <p style="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL;text-align:justify">Directors must be elected by a majority of the votes cast in elections for which the number of nominees for election does not exceed the number of directors to be elected. A plurality vote standard applies to contested elections where the number of nominees exceeds the number of directors to be elected. Our Bylaws provide that any incumbent director who does not receive a majority of the votes cast in an uncontested election is required to tender his or her resignation for consideration by our Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee. The Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee will make a recommendation to the Board whether to accept or reject the resignation, or whether other action should be taken. The director who tenders his or her resignation will not participate in the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee&#8217;s or the Board&#8217;s decision. In determining its recommendation to the Board, the Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee will consider all factors that it deems relevant. Following such determination, we will promptly publicly disclose the Board&#8217;s decision, including, if applicable, the reasons for rejecting the tendered resignation. </p>
 <p style="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&#160;</p>
